description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting and challenging opportunity has arisen for an experienced Occupational Therapist to join our Outpatient Upper Limb Therapy Team. High level clinical reasoning, risk identification and problem solving skills are essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We wish to recruit a highly skilled and dynamic senior clinician who must have significant experience and clinical skills and a clear understanding of the therapist role in upper limb pathways. The post holder must demonstrate the ability to lead a team which delivers innovative, responsive services to meet both the needs of the patients and the organisation. The role requires excellent communication skills and the ability to work as an effective member of the wider Therapies Team and MDT. The post holder will have significant experience working with complex upper limb presentations. The successful candidate will demonstrate confidence in managing a varied workload in a challenging and fast paced environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to staff development and training through regular supervision, appraisal and personalised development plans. You will be responsible for the supervision and support of junior staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder would be required to work flexibly across all Trust sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clare Collie (Outpatient Therapies Manager) clare.collie@liverpoolft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fiona Cashin (Clinical Specialist Occupational Therapist) fiona.cashin@liverpoolft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
